This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Plea/sentencing hearing on November 21, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
PLEAS scheduled for 11/21/22 at 3:30 pm with Atty Carson. Parties notified by email. Notice sent to DE.

Attorney Dan Tombasco appeared for the State. Defendant appeared with Attorney Carson.  Clerk HM.  State is compliant with victim rights notification.  Court does not accept plea agreement.  PLEAS set over to Br. 6 - attys to contact clerk for new date.  Bond continued.

3:01 PM Attorney Daniel Joseph Tombasco in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Destinee Shalane Hingleton in court.  Attorney Christopher Scott Carson appeared by phone for Destinee Shalane Hingleton. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: Clerk had to call Attorney Carson as the DE has been here since 2 pm and DE's mother took off work for today's hearing. Attorney Carson states this hearing was not on his calendar and apologized to the Court. Attorney Carson states the matter is resolved. Court will adjourn so Attorney Carson may review the plea questionnaire/ waiver of rights form with the DE. Attorney Carson shall appear early and in person for the next hearing. Attorney Carson offers to reimburse the DE's mother for the lost wages she has incurred.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 1, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

01:47 PM   Attorney Dan Tombasco appeared for the State. Defendant, Destinee Shalane Hingleton, appeared with Attorney Christopher Scott Carson.   Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES:   Victim rights compliance. Attorney Carson is requesting an adjournment as he needs additional time to review the discovery with the DE. Attorney Carson also advises the Court that he received an offer from the State and believes the matter will be resolved at the next hearing. State does not object. Court adjourns.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 21, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
